  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "WCW Wrestling (a.k.a. WCW World Championship Wrestling) is a Nintendo Entertainment System professional wrestling video game that was originally released in Japan in 1989 under the name Super Star Pro Wrestling. It was later released in North America in 1990 with a mostly different lineup of wrestlers.\nIt was the first (and, to date, only) video game based on the National Wrestling Alliance (at the time, WCW was a member of NWA). After The Road Warriors joined the World Wrestling Federation, WCW continued to advertise the game in their own catalogs with a mock-up cartridge showing Sting on the label, though no such copies of the game with an alternate label are known to exist or believed to have ever been manufactured. To date, the game has sold over 100,000 copies.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
